<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870506-0011 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:</HL><SO>  </SO><IN> U.S. TOBACCO CO. </IN><TEXT>05/06/87WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)UST   U.S. TOBACCO CO., Greenwich, Conn., said shareholders voted to reorganize the concern into a holding company named UST Inc. that will be the parent of U.S. Tobacco and its subsidiaries. Company units sell smokeless tobacco products, cigars and table wines. Under the reorganization, holders of U.S. Tobacco became holders of UST. The plan became effective yesterday following the company's annual and board meetings. </TEXT></DOC>